66class RtpVideoStreamReceiver2 : public LossNotificationSender,
67 public RecoveredPacketReceiver,
68 public RtpPacketSinkInterface,
69 public KeyFrameRequestSender,
70 public OnCompleteFrameCallback,
71 public OnDecryptedFrameCallback,
72 public OnDecryptionStatusChangeCallback,
73 public RtpVideoFrameReceiver {
74 public:
75 RtpVideoStreamReceiver2(
76 TaskQueueBase* current_queue,
77 Clock* clock,
78 Transport* transport,
79 RtcpRttStats* rtt_stats,
80 // The packet router is optional; if provided, the RtpRtcp module for this
81 // stream is registered as a candidate for sending REMB and transport
82 // feedback.
83 PacketRouter* packet_router,
84 const VideoReceiveStream::Config* config,
85 ReceiveStatistics* rtp_receive_statistics,
86 RtcpPacketTypeCounterObserver* rtcp_packet_type_counter_observer,
87 RtcpCnameCallback* rtcp_cname_callback,
88 ProcessThread* process_thread,
89 NackSender* nack_sender,
90 // The KeyFrameRequestSender is optional; if not provided, key frame
91 // requests are sent via the internal RtpRtcp module.
92 KeyFrameRequestSender* keyframe_request_sender,
93 OnCompleteFrameCallback* complete_frame_callback,
94 rtc::scoped_refptr<FrameDecryptorInterface> frame_decryptor,
95 rtc::scoped_refptr<FrameTransformerInterface> frame_transformer);
96 ~RtpVideoStreamReceiver2() override;
97
98 void AddReceiveCodec(uint8_t payload_type,
99 const VideoCodec& video_codec,
100 const std::map<std::string, std::string>& codec_params,
101 bool raw_payload);
102
103 void StartReceive();
104 void StopReceive();
105
106 // Produces the transport-related timestamps; current_delay_ms is left unset.
107 absl::optional<Syncable::Info> GetSyncInfo() const;
108
109 bool DeliverRtcp(const uint8_t* rtcp_packet, size_t rtcp_packet_length);
110
111 void FrameContinuous(int64_t seq_num);
112
113 void FrameDecoded(int64_t seq_num);
114
115 void SignalNetworkState(NetworkState state);
116
117 // Returns number of different frames seen.
118 int GetUniqueFramesSeen() const {
119 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&worker_task_checker_);
120 return frame_counter_.GetUniqueSeen();
121 }
122
123 // Implements RtpPacketSinkInterface.
124 void OnRtpPacket(const RtpPacketReceived& packet) override;
125
126 // Public only for tests.
127 void OnReceivedPayloadData(rtc::CopyOnWriteBuffer codec_payload,
128 const RtpPacketReceived& rtp_packet,
129 const RTPVideoHeader& video);
130
131 // Implements RecoveredPacketReceiver.
132 void OnRecoveredPacket(const uint8_t* packet, size_t packet_length) override;
133
134 // Send an RTCP keyframe request.
135 void RequestKeyFrame() override;
136
137 // Implements LossNotificationSender.
138 void SendLossNotification(uint16_t last_decoded_seq_num,
139 uint16_t last_received_seq_num,
140 bool decodability_flag,
141 bool buffering_allowed) override;
142
143 bool IsUlpfecEnabled() const;
144 bool IsRetransmissionsEnabled() const;
145
146 // Returns true if a decryptor is attached and frames can be decrypted.
147 // Updated by OnDecryptionStatusChangeCallback. Note this refers to Frame
148 // Decryption not SRTP.
149 bool IsDecryptable() const;
150
151 // Don't use, still experimental.
152 void RequestPacketRetransmit(const std::vector<uint16_t>& sequence_numbers);
153
154 // Implements OnCompleteFrameCallback.
155 void OnCompleteFrame(std::unique_ptr<EncodedFrame> frame) override;
156
157 // Implements OnDecryptedFrameCallback.
158 void OnDecryptedFrame(std::unique_ptr<RtpFrameObject> frame) override;
159
160 // Implements OnDecryptionStatusChangeCallback.
161 void OnDecryptionStatusChange(
162 FrameDecryptorInterface::Status status) override;
163
164 // Optionally set a frame decryptor after a stream has started. This will not
165 // reset the decoder state.
166 void SetFrameDecryptor(
167 rtc::scoped_refptr<FrameDecryptorInterface> frame_decryptor);
168
169 // Sets a frame transformer after a stream has started, if no transformer
170 // has previously been set. Does not reset the decoder state.
171 void SetDepacketizerToDecoderFrameTransformer(
172 rtc::scoped_refptr<FrameTransformerInterface> frame_transformer);
173
174 // Called by VideoReceiveStream when stats are updated.
175 void UpdateRtt(int64_t max_rtt_ms);
176
177 absl::optional<int64_t> LastReceivedPacketMs() const;
178 absl::optional<int64_t> LastReceivedKeyframePacketMs() const;
179
180 private:
181 // Implements RtpVideoFrameReceiver.
182 void ManageFrame(std::unique_ptr<RtpFrameObject> frame) override;
183
184 // Used for buffering RTCP feedback messages and sending them all together.
185 // Note:
186 // 1. Key frame requests and NACKs are mutually exclusive, with the
187 // former taking precedence over the latter.
188 // 2. Loss notifications are orthogonal to either. (That is, may be sent
189 // alongside either.)
190 class RtcpFeedbackBuffer : public KeyFrameRequestSender,
191 public NackSender,
192 public LossNotificationSender {
193 public:
194 RtcpFeedbackBuffer(KeyFrameRequestSender* key_frame_request_sender,
195 NackSender* nack_sender,
196 LossNotificationSender* loss_notification_sender);
197
198 ~RtcpFeedbackBuffer() override = default;
199
200 // KeyFrameRequestSender implementation.
201 void RequestKeyFrame() override;
202
203 // NackSender implementation.
204 void SendNack(const std::vector<uint16_t>& sequence_numbers,
205 bool buffering_allowed) override;
206
207 // LossNotificationSender implementation.
208 void SendLossNotification(uint16_t last_decoded_seq_num,
209 uint16_t last_received_seq_num,
210 bool decodability_flag,
211 bool buffering_allowed) override;
212
213 // Send all RTCP feedback messages buffered thus far.
214 void SendBufferedRtcpFeedback();
215
216 private:
217 // LNTF-related state.
218 struct LossNotificationState {
219 LossNotificationState(uint16_t last_decoded_seq_num,
220 uint16_t last_received_seq_num,
221 bool decodability_flag)
222 : last_decoded_seq_num(last_decoded_seq_num),
223 last_received_seq_num(last_received_seq_num),
224 decodability_flag(decodability_flag) {}
225
226 uint16_t last_decoded_seq_num;
227 uint16_t last_received_seq_num;
228 bool decodability_flag;
229 };

232 KeyFrameRequestSender* const key_frame_request_sender_;
233 NackSender* const nack_sender_;
234 LossNotificationSender* const loss_notification_sender_;
235
236 // Key-frame-request-related state.
237 bool request_key_frame_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(worker_task_checker_);
238
239 // NACK-related state.
240 std::vector<uint16_t> nack_sequence_numbers_
241 RTC_GUARDED_BY(worker_task_checker_);
242
243 absl::optional<LossNotificationState> lntf_state_
244 RTC_GUARDED_BY(worker_task_checker_);
245 };

247 kDropPacket,
248 kHasGenericDescriptor,
249 kNoGenericDescriptor
250 };

252 // Entry point doing non-stats work for a received packet. Called
253 // for the same packet both before and after RED decapsulation.
254 void ReceivePacket(const RtpPacketReceived& packet);
255 // Parses and handles RED headers.
256 // This function assumes that it's being called from only one thread.

265 RTPVideoHeader* video_header) RTC_RUN_ON(worker_task_checker_);
266 void OnAssembledFrame(std::unique_ptr<RtpFrameObject> frame);
267 void UpdatePacketReceiveTimestamps(const RtpPacketReceived& packet,
268 bool is_keyframe)
269 RTC_RUN_ON(worker_task_checker_);
